@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "IsoGate" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game board consists of an 8 by 8 tiles area where a number of
'gates' are placed. An 'X' shape is placed at the upper left
position on the board and the exit tile, indicated by a small box,
is located at the lower right on the game board. 'Arrows',
represented by small triangles, are placed around the game board.

  Each arrow will move one or more gates, according to the row or
column that arrow is located (the arrows located at the left and
right of the game board will move the corresponding horizontal
gates and the arrows located above and below the game board will
move the corresponding vertical gates). When gates are at their
limit of travel, the corresponding arrows will not show.

  To play, click on an arrow that is located around the game board,
this will move, by one position, all corresponding gates. To move
the X shape, it must be surrounded by gates and/or one or more of
the game board's edges, so there is only one opening where the
X shape can go.

  From time to time, just to complicate things, some gates will
randomly move...

  If you get stuck, you can restart a game board by clicking on the
'New Game' button. But be aware that the amount of moves you make
for the current game board is added up until you complete it...

NOTE: You can change the colour of the X shape simply by clicking
      on it.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

